Real-world examples of possible Figment applications.

Embedding Haskell syntax:

factorial 0 = 1
factorial n = n * factorial (n - 1)

Writing Caterwaul-style programs:

l[x = 1, y = 2][z.foo = x + y]
x /se[console.log(x)]

Operating as CSS:

div.foo {font-family: sans-serif}
div#bar > .bif {font-weight: bold}

Operating as markup:

div.foo('bar')

Destructuring binds (assuming low precedence of |):

map(f, xs) = x::xs' -> f(x) :: map(f, xs')
           | []     -> []

UI layout:

/window = top: close title tabs
        | tab(...)
        | tab(...)

Vaguely normal Javascript:

while (i1 < i2) {
  while (xs[i1] > pivot) ++i1 ;
  while (xs[i2] < pivot) --i2 ;
}

Parsing stuff:

expr ::= term op expr     where op <- qw[+ - * / ^]
term ::= literal [* term] where literal = qr \d+

Macroexpansion:

fn[x][console.log(x), x](x) when x /debug

Perl-style programming:

map[_ + 1], keys xs
